{{DISPLAYTITLE:Level 251: "Unstable Bricks"}}

<center><font size="8"> Brick Heaven</font></center>


{{Class Custom Image|class=3e - Environmental|hexagon=🧱|color=#75623e|safety=Unsafe|security=Partially Unstable|entity=Dangerous Weather Conditions|bg-image=Bricks.jpg}}
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
<center><font size="7">| General Description |</font></center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
{{Blurimage|file=Level 251.jpg|hovertext=Long linen sheets|caption=Where Am I Going??}}
'''Level 251, also known as "Unstable Bricks" or "Bricks And Beyond", is described as a large town consisting almost entirely of brick structures. The level appears to resemble an old urban settlement, with countless buildings stretching far into the distance. Nearly every visible structure is constructed from red, brown, or occasionally darkened brick. The town appears to extend for a seemingly endless distance, with rows of buildings repeating across the horizon.'''

'''Most buildings within Level 251 resemble small residential houses or narrow townhouses. These houses are typically two to three stories tall and are built primarily from tightly packed brick walls supported by wooden and concrete structural elements. The roofs are usually constructed from dark tiles or reinforced wooden beams. Windows are commonly present on most buildings, though many appear dusty, cracked, or partially sealed. Some windows are completely dark, making it impossible to see inside the buildings.'''

'''Alleys are located between most houses, forming narrow pathways that run throughout the town. These alleys often connect to wider brick streets, creating a large network of walkways and corridors. The streets themselves are typically paved with old brick or stone tiles, which appear worn but still structurally stable. Some alleys are extremely narrow, forcing wanderers to move carefully through them. In many areas, these passageways form maze-like layouts that can make navigation difficult.'''

'''The environment of Level 251 is dominated by brick materials. Walls, sidewalks, fences, chimneys, and even small decorative structures are constructed almost entirely from brick. In some locations, large brick towers or warehouse-like buildings can be seen rising above the surrounding houses. Despite the repetitive architecture, small variations in building design can occasionally be observed, such as different brick colors, minor structural damage, or unusual building shapes.'''

'''The temperature within Level 251 typically remains between 14°C and 21°C (57°F–69°F). The climate is generally calm and stable, though the air often feels slightly dry and dusty due to the large amount of exposed brick and stone. Gentle winds may occasionally move through the narrow streets and alleys, producing faint echoing sounds as they pass between the buildings.'''

'''Lighting within the level usually resembles late afternoon daylight. The sky above the town is often covered by a pale gray or slightly orange hue, though the exact source of light is unclear. Shadows stretch across the brick streets and between the buildings, creating long dark corridors throughout the town. At night-like periods, the level becomes significantly darker, and the narrow alleys can become difficult to navigate.'''

'''Very little vegetation exists within Level 251. In rare cases, small weeds or patches of grass may grow between cracks in the brick pavement. Occasionally, dead vines or dried plants can be seen climbing along the sides of certain buildings. However, large trees or gardens are rare within the level.'''

{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
<center><font size="7">| Day |</font></center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
{{Blurimage|file=Level 251 Day.jpg|hovertext=Long linen sheets|caption=Day Time}}
'''During the daytime, Level 251 becomes significantly more hostile due to rapidly changing weather conditions. The sky often becomes bright and clear, with a powerful sun shining directly above the town. The sunlight reflects strongly off the countless brick surfaces, causing the environment to heat up quickly. During these periods, the temperature can rise dramatically, often reaching between 32°C and 41°C (89°F–105°F). The intense heat can make long periods of exploration physically exhausting for wanderers.'''

'''Atmospheric pressure within the level can also change rapidly during the day. Barometric pressure readings have been recorded fluctuating between 980 hPa and 1035 hPa within short periods of time. These sudden pressure changes often signal incoming severe weather events. Wanderers may notice strong gusts of wind forming in the narrow brick streets, sometimes producing loud whistling sounds as the air moves through the tight alleys and between buildings.'''

'''One of the most dangerous phenomena during the daytime is the frequent development of severe storms. Large supercell thunderstorms can occasionally form above the town, often developing quickly with little warning. These storms are capable of producing extremely powerful tornadoes that move through the streets and between the buildings. The tornadoes can rip apart weaker brick structures, collapse chimneys, and scatter debris throughout the surrounding area.'''
{{Blurimage|file=Level 251 Tornado damage.jpg|hovertext=Long linen sheets|caption=A House Hit By An EF1}}
'''In some cases, Level 251 may experience full tornado outbreaks. During these events, multiple tornadoes can form at the same time across different parts of the town. These tornadoes may vary greatly in size and intensity, ranging from smaller funnel tornadoes to large wedge-shaped storms capable of causing widespread destruction. The narrow layout of the town can cause winds to accelerate between buildings, making these tornadoes even more dangerous for anyone caught outside.'''

