{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
<center><font size="7">| Night |</font></center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
{{Blurimage|file=Level 251 Night.jpg|hovertext=Long linen sheets|caption=Something Is Odd???}}
'''During nighttime, the environment of Level 251 changes noticeably. As the sun disappears beyond the horizon, temperatures across the brick town begin to drop rapidly. The temperature typically falls to between 6°C and 12°C (42°F–53°F), creating a cool and sometimes uncomfortable atmosphere for wanderers still outside. The brick structures, which absorbed large amounts of heat during the day, slowly release it throughout the night, occasionally producing faint cracking or popping sounds within the walls.'''

'''As darkness settles over the town, the streets and alleys become significantly harder to navigate. However, many of the streetlights located throughout the level will automatically turn on. These lights are mounted on tall metal poles placed along the sidewalks and intersections of the town. The streetlights emit a dim yellow or orange glow, illuminating small sections of the brick streets while leaving large portions of the alleys and side paths in deep shadow. The lights appear to function without any visible electrical source and rarely malfunction.'''

'''During this time, [[Entity 3]] commonly known as Smilers become far more active within the level. Smilers often emerge from dark alleyways, abandoned buildings, and poorly lit corners of the streets. Their glowing faces can sometimes be seen staring from the darkness just beyond the reach of the streetlights. Because the lighting in the level leaves many areas in shadow, Smilers are able to move and hide easily throughout the town.'''

'''Encounters with Smilers are significantly more common at night. Wanderers are advised to remain within well-lit areas whenever possible and to avoid entering dark alleys or unlit sections of the town. Remaining close to functioning streetlights may reduce the chances of direct encounters with these entities. Despite this precaution, the large number of shadows created by the brick buildings makes nighttime travel through Level 251 particularly dangerous.'''
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
<center><font size="7">| Entities & Dangers |</font></center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
==Tornadoes==
{{Entity Class|Agg=2|Int=2|Dan=5|no=74|Hab=Windy or outdoor levels}}
'''[[Entity 74]], commonly referred to as Tornadoes, are very common within Level 251 and are considered one of the most dangerous environmental hazards present in the level. These phenomena primarily occur during the daytime, when atmospheric conditions across the brick town become highly unstable.
{{Blurimage|file=Level 251 Tornado damage 4.png|hovertext=Long linen sheets|caption=A two-story building struck by an EF4 tornado}}
'''During the day, large supercell thunderstorms frequently develop above the level. These storms often move slowly across the town, producing intense weather conditions including extremely strong winds, large hail, heavy rainfall, and powerful tornadoes. The storms typically form with little warning, although wanderers may occasionally notice darkening skies, sudden pressure drops, or strong gusts of wind before a storm begins to fully develop.'''

'''The tornadoes produced by these storms can vary greatly in size and intensity. Some appear as narrow funnel-shaped tornadoes that move quickly between the brick streets, while others form massive wedge-shaped storms that can span several city blocks at once. Because of the tight layout of the town and the many narrow streets, wind speeds can increase dramatically as the tornadoes move between buildings. This effect often causes debris to be thrown violently through the streets and alleys.'''

'''In many cases, these storms also produce extremely large hailstones that can damage windows, rooftops, and weaker brick structures. Heavy rain is also common during these events, often reducing visibility throughout the town. Combined with the strong winds, these conditions can make it extremely difficult for wanderers to safely navigate the streets during a storm.'''

'''Occasionally, Level 251 may experience full tornado outbreaks. During these events, multiple tornadoes can form across different sections of the town simultaneously. These outbreaks may last for extended periods of time and can cause widespread destruction throughout the brick structures of the level. Large sections of buildings may collapse, and debris from damaged structures can scatter across the streets.'''

'''Because tornadoes frequently travel unpredictably through the town’s layout of narrow streets and alleys, avoiding them can be extremely difficult. Wanderers are strongly advised to seek shelter inside the most structurally stable brick buildings available if severe storms begin to form. However, even these structures may not always survive the strongest tornadoes produced within the level.'''
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
==Smilers==
{{Entity Class|Agg=5|Int=5|Dan=5|no=3|Hab=Dark areas of any level}}
'''[[Entity 3]], commonly referred to as Smilers, are one of the most frequently encountered entities in Level 251, especially during nighttime.'''

'''Smilers tend to emerge primarily after sunset, when the level becomes dim and streetlights cast long shadows across the brick town. They are often observed lurking in alleys, peering around corners, or standing motionless in darkened doorways. Their movement is typically slow and deliberate when they are stalking, but they can move with sudden bursts of speed if a wanderer comes too close. Despite this, Smilers rarely engage in direct attacks unless provoked or approached aggressively.'''

'''The behavior of Smilers is highly unpredictable. Some will simply observe wanderers from a distance, maintaining their eerie, wide grin, while others have been reported following wanderers through streets and alleyways for extended periods. They appear to enjoy remaining in poorly lit areas, using shadows and the environment to conceal their movements. Smilers are also capable of appearing in open spaces if the lighting conditions are favorable, making them particularly dangerous in areas where visibility is reduced.'''

{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
<center><font size="7">| Colonies & Outposts |</font></center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
'''Due to the extreme weather conditions, no colonies or outposts have been successfully established within the level. Any attempts to create permanent settlements have resulted in total destruction, usually caused by violent tornadoes.'''
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
<center><font size="7">| Entrances and Exits |</font></center>
{{Underline|FFFFFF}}
===Entrances===
*'''Nocliping through a brick on any level may lead here.
*'''Damaging a house on [[Level 9]] with a brick may lead here.
*'''Hitting an entity with a brick on [[Level 442]] may lead here.
===Exits===
*'''Finding a white house and opening the front door may send one to [[Level 20]].
*'''Nocliping through a tree may lead to [[Level 110]].
*'''Surviving a major tornado outbreak may lead to [[Level 9.99]].
